  "body": "**Is this a BUG REPORT or FEATURE REQUEST?**:\r\nThis is request for improvements.\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nWhen PodSecurityPolicy provider validates `SecurityContext.SupplementalGroups` or `fsGroup` fields of a pod, it shows an error like \"999 is not an allowed group\" if the group doesn't belong to the range(s).\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nIt should include to the error message also the allowed values -- the ranges against what we were validating this group. This will simplify user experience and debugging.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n- run kubernetes cluster with PSP support\r\n- create a PSP that allows fsGroup/SupplementalGroups in some ranges\r\n- grant to a user access to this PSP\r\n- try to create a pod that has fsGroup/SupplementalGroups outside of the allowed ranges\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\nIn order to improve the current behavior, we need to modify `Validate()` function here: https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/48a7048d9819ee516b3cfdf5c458b5815b640138/pkg/security/podsecuritypolicy/group/mustrunas.go#L71-L76\r\n\r\nReported-by: @dmage \r\n\r\n@kubernetes/sig-auth-feature-requests \r\n/kind help",
